## ðŸ”¥ â€œWow Factorâ€
Advanced Splunk apps were installed and configured to simulate professional SOC workflows:

- **Splunk Security Essentials**
  - Automated phishing indicators
  - Threat investigation playbooks
  - Account compromise analytics

- **Cyber Security Essentials App**
  - Live threat dashboards
  - APT groups, malware categories, triggered alerts

- **Windows 11 Host Monitoring**
  - Restart/shutdown tracking
  - Stability and compromise detection

---

## ðŸ§© Key Findings
- Multiple SSH brute-force attempts detected and mapped by region
- Suspicious late-night health app logs indicating automation misuse
- High-volume Apache traffic suggesting scanning activity
- System wake events and USB behavior on Mac indicating possible reconnaissance

---

## ðŸ›¡ï¸ Security Recommendations
| Improvement | Benefit |
|------------|---------|
| MFA & stricter authentication | Reduce credential compromise |
| USB device restrictions | Prevent data exfiltration |
| Alerting on geo-based SSH anomalies | Faster threat response |
| Firmware + OS updates | Improve endpoint resilience |
| Log retention & centralization | Better forensic readiness |

